756. Ihm», fourth king of Troy, founded Ilion and received from Jupiter the famous Palladium. He was the son of Tros, father of Laomedon, and grandfather of Priam.

Assaracus: son of Tros, father of Capys, and grandfather of Anchises. The genealog-y given here is not a striet descent from father to son. Ilus, Assaracus, and Ganymede were brothers ; Laomedon was the son of Ilus, and Priam was the son of Laomedon.

756. Ganymedes, a beautiful youth of Phrygia, son of Tros, was, when hunting on Mount Ida, carried away by an eagle to Jupiter and made cup-bearer to the gods.

757. Priamus: the last king of Troy, son of Laomedon, father of Hector and Paris, and husband of Hecuba. Troy was besieged for 10 years by the united Greeks on account of Paris’ rape of Helen.
